    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "This is deliberate, because the point of ctrl-Enter is a sort of 'terminal mode', where you just want to execute some code, but not actually preserve it in the notebook.  The reason the input is selected is so that you can just start typing and the previous input will be replaced.  For the same reason that ctrl-Enter makes it mildly inconvenient to _not_ replace text, failing to select it all makes it inconvenient to replace it, which is the expressed goal of ctrl-Enter.\n\nWhat are you using ctrl-Enter for if you want to preserve the contents of the cell but also not move on to the next cell?\n\nWe've guessed at common use cases, and the UI has been driven by the desires of the developers as they use it, but it's always helpful to hear how people are using it for whom our decisions are not ideal.\n"
  },
