    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Cognitively, moving to some other cell further down the page is different than moving to the very next cell.\nAlso, I do also run a few lines of code, making small modifications until I get what I expect as the output (e.g. when tweaking the layout of a plot). I'm always working on that block of code, and I always intend to make only small modifications. \n\nPerhaps if the input in a cell is just one line, select it after ctrl+enter? Otherwise, return the cursor to where it was?\n"
