    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The selection of the text is deliberate as we want it to be easy to\nquickly remove the old output if desired.  Here is a rough description\nof that logic in the ideal case:\n- When ctrl-enter is given we run the cell and select the previous\n  input.  The cell is also given keyboard focus so you can start typing\n  into the cell immediately.\n- If you type a R or L arrow key the text will deselect and you can\n  edit it in any way you want.  A single mouse click in the cell will\n  also deselect the text.\n- If you type most other characters, it selected text will be deleted\n  and you start from scratch.\n\n> To de-select the text, I have to double-click, which selects the nearest word, and then click or ctrl+n or arrow-down to move away from the word selection. Single-clicking, or using the arrows does not work after hitting ctrl+enter.\n\nThis is a bug then.  What browser/platform are you on?\n\n## \n\nBrian E. Granger\nCal Poly State University, San Luis Obispo\nbgranger@calpoly.edu and ellisonbg@gmail.com\n"
  },
